The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Pak Senate summons board officials 
Islamabad: Pakistan cricket officials will explain to the countrys Senate the reasons for the home teams defeat against India on Saturday. The Senate chairman Mohammadmian Soomro may also attend the sports and cultural committee meeting which summoned PCB chairman Shaharyar Khan, chief executive Rameez Raja and chairman of selectors Wasim Bari. Yes, we have been summoned before the committee and it is routine that any committee seeking clarification on anything calls the concerned officials and we will go there with open minds, said Shaharyar. We realise peoples disappointment over the defeat but we have started our planning for the future to build a strong team, he said. A member of the committee Enver Baig said the whole nation is concerned over defeat against India.  (PTI)  Copyright 
